      "text": [
        " أَمِيرُ اَلْمُؤْمِنِينَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ لِشُرَيْحٍ : \"يَا شُرَيْحُ لاَ تُسَارَّ أَحَداً فِي مَجْلِسِكَ وَ إِذَا غَضِبْتَ فَقُمْ وَ لاَ تَقْضِيَنَّ وَ أَنْتَ غَضْبَانُ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3239 - Commander of the Faithful Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) said to Shurayh:\n\"O Shurayh, do not speak privately with anyone in your court. And if you become angry, stand up and do not pass judgment while you are angry.\""
        ]
      }
    },
